Task:
Create a cron job:
$ ssh tony@stapp01 
$ sudo su 
$ yum install cronie -y
$ systemctl start crond.service
$ systemctl status crond.service
$ crontab -e
$ crontab -l
$ ll /tmp/
Repeat same for the rest two application servers

Task: Linux User Files
$ ssh steve@stapp02
provide password
$ sudo su
password
$ ll /home/usersdata
$ ll /media
$ find /home/usersdata/ -type f -user kirsty |wc -l
$ find /home/usersdata/ -type f -user kirsty -exec cp --parent {} /media \; 
Ref: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2961673/find-missing-argument-to-exec
$ ll /media/home/usersdata/

Task: Linux User Without Home
$ ssh steve@stapp02
provide password then login as root user 
$ sudo su
$ id rose
$ cat /etc/passwd/ |grep rose
$ useradd -M rose
$ id rose
$ cat /etc/passwd/ |grep rose
$ ll /home/ 

Task: substitution of string in a file
$ ssh clint@stbkp01 then provide password as usual
$ sudo su login as root user
$ cat /root/nautilus.xml
$ sed -i 's/String/Topedo/g' /root/nautilus.xml

Task: Linux Banner
$ ll /home/thor/nautilus_banner
$ scp -r /home/thor/nautilus tony@stapp01:/tmp
$ ssh -t tony@stapp01 'sudo mv /tmp/nautilus_banner /etc/motd'
provide passwords as usual

In this task we need to install openssh-clients package for the database server.
$ ssh peter@stdb01 and enter password
$ sudo yum install openssh-clients

$ scp -r /home/thor/nautilus peter@stdb01:/tmp
$ ssh -t peter@stdb01 'sudo mv /tmp/nautilus_banner /etc/motd'
$ scp -r /home/thor/nautilus steve@stapp02:/tmp
$ ssh -t steve@stapp02 'sudo mv /tmp/nautilus_banner /etc/motd'
$ scp -r /home/thor/nautilus banner@stapp03:/tmp
$ ssh -t banner@stapp03 'sudo mv /tmp/nautilus_banner /etc/motd'



